`Entity` is an abstract class that serves as a base of all entity behavior.
As it's abstract, it cannot be directly constructed. Other entity classes extend from this class.

# How to get Entities

`Entity` objects are usually obtained as a result of either:
- spawning an entity, for example via the `[js]spawnEntity()` instance method on [[/concepts/level/Level|`Level`]] or `[js]createEntity()` instance method on [[/concepts/block/LevelBlock|`LevelBlock`]],
- searching for an entity in world, for example via `[js]getEntities()` instance method on [[/concepts/level/Level|`Level`]] or `[js]getPlayersInRange()` instance method on [[/concepts/block/LevelBlock|`LevelBlock`]].

# Instance methods

>>> #invulnerable-info
>>> info
Entities are invulnerable to all damages, if they are removed from the world.
Entities that are invulnerable to all damages can also be only damaged by void damage or Creative mode players.
<<<
<<<

>>> info
Only a select subset of all public methods will be documented here.
<<<

In the following examples, `[js]entity` will be referring to the instance of `Entity`.

