## Relation

>>> #closerThan
### `closerThan`
<<<

>>> #closerThan-description

**Syntax**
```js
entity.closerThan(otherEntity, distance)
entity.closerThan(otherEntity, horizontalDistance, verticalDistance)
```

Checks, whether `[js]otherEntity` is within a cylinder-shaped area of `[js]horizontalDistance` radius and `[js]2 * verticalDistance` height centered at the `[js]entity`.

**Parameters**
- `[js]otherEntity`: The `Entity` to check.
- `[js]distance`: If there are no more arguments past this one, specifies both the horizontal and vertical distance to search (in blocks).
- `[js]horizontalDistance`: The horizontal distance (that is: radius of the cylinder, in blocks) to search from the `entity`.
- `[js]verticalDistance`: The vertical distance (that is: half of the cylinder's height, in blocks) to search from the `entity`.

**Return value**
`[js]true` if `[js]otherEntity` is within range, `[js]false` otherwise.
<<<

| <#closerThan> |
| <#closerThan-description> |
---

>>> #distanceTo
### `distanceTo`
<<<

>>> #distanceTo-description

**Syntax**
```js
entity.distanceTo(otherEntity)
```

Returns the distance of `[js]entity` to `[js]otherEntity`.

**Parameters**
- `[js]otherEntity`: The `Entity` to measure distance to.
**Return value**
The distance to `[js]otherEntity`.
<<<

| <#distanceTo> |
| <#distanceTo-description> |
---

>>> #getDistanceSq
### `getDistanceSq`
<<<

>>> #getDistanceSq-description

>>> info
This overload has its name changed from vanilla: `distanceToSqr`.
<<<

**Syntax**
```js
entity.getDistanceSq(x, y, z)
```

Returns the **squared** distance of `[js]entity` to a point in 3D space specified by `[js]x`, `[js]y` and `[js]z` coordinates.

In case of sorting entities by distance, sorting by squares of distances is more efficient than sorting by distances, because there's no need to take a square root of the squared distance.

**Parameters**
- `[js]x`, `[js]y`, `[js]z`: The coordinates of point in 3D space to measure distance to.
**Return value**
The **square** of distance to a point in 3D space.
<<<

| <#getDistanceSq> |
| <#getDistanceSq-description> |
---

>>> #distanceToEntitySqr
### `distanceToEntitySqr`
<<<

>>> #distanceToEntitySqr-description

>>> info
This overload has its name changed from vanilla: `distanceToSqr`.
<<<

**Syntax**
```js
entity.distanceToEntitySqr(otherEntity)
```

Returns the **squared** distance of `[js]entity` to `[js]otherEntity`.
In case of sorting entities by distance, sorting by squares of distances is more efficient than sorting by distances, because there's no need to take a square root of the squared distance.

**Parameters**
- `[js]otherEntity`: The `Entity` to measure distance to.
**Return value**
The **square** of distance to `[js]otherEntity`.
<<<

| <#distanceToEntitySqr> |
| <#distanceToEntitySqr-description> |
---

>>> #distanceToSqr
### `distanceToSqr`
<<<

>>> #distanceToSqr-description

**Syntax**
```js
entity.distanceToSqr(positionVector)
```

Returns the **squared** distance of `[js]entity` to a point in 3D space specified by a given position vector.

In case of sorting entities by distance, sorting by squares of distances is more efficient than sorting by distances, because there's no need to take a square root of the squared distance.

**Parameters**
- `[js]positionVector`: {vec3} representing the position of a point in 3D space. It may be a 3-element JS array representing the vector, like `[js]\[64, 50, -20\]`.
**Return value**
The **square** of distance to a point in 3D space.
<<<

| <#distanceToSqr> |
| <#distanceToSqr-description> |
