entity['spawnAtLocation(net.minecraft.world.level.ItemLike,int)'](item, offsetY)
entity['spawnAtLocation(net.minecraft.world.item.ItemStack)'](itemStack)
entity['spawnAtLocation(net.minecraft.world.item.ItemStack,float)'](itemStack, offsetY)
```

Spawns an item entity at the position of the `[js]entity`, optionally moved up/down by the specified `[js]offsetY`. The spawned item entity will gain random momentum.

**Parameters**

- `[js]item`: Instance of anything that can be represented as an item.
This includes [[/concepts/block/Block|`Block`]], [[/concepts/item|`Item`]] and anything derived from those classes, like [[/concepts/block/BlockState|`BlockState`]], [[/concepts/item-stack|`ItemStack`]], etc.
It may be a string representing an item, for example `[js]'minecraft:oak_log'`.
- `[js]itemStack`: An [[/concepts/item-stack|`ItemStack`]].
It may be a string representing an item stack, for example `[js]'2x minecraft:oak_log'`.
- `[js]offsetY` {optional}:
  - If `[js]item` was specified, it's an **integer** representing the Y offset of the newly spawned item entity relative to the position of `[js]entity`.
  - If `[js]itemStack` was specified, it's a **floating-point number** representing the Y offset of the newly spawned item entity relative to the position of `[js]entity`.
**Return value**
The reference to the [[/concepts/entity/ItemEntity|`ItemEntity`]] spawned.
